HMT: Hierarchical Memory Tree for Web Agents

This repository contains an HMT implementation and lightweight adapters for web-agent benchmarks.
It includes:

- hierarchical intent-stage-action memory records;
- condition-aware stage selection;
- semantic action descriptors that avoid transferable source-site IDs;
- DOM/accessibility preprocessing for observation summaries;
- Mind2Web and WebArena entry points;
- GPT-4 prompt templates and local Qwen embedding/reranking adapters.

No benchmark data, API keys, WebArena credentials, or private server URLs are included.
